{"variants":[{"paths":["\/tutorials\/buildingsyncups"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"overview","sections":[{"kind":"hero","title":"Building SyncUps","action":{"overridingTitle":"Get started","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Get started"}],"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps"},"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The SyncUps application is a recreation of one of Apple’s more interesting demo applications,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Scrumdinger. We recreate it from scratch using the Composable Architecture, with a focus on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"domain modeling, controlling dependencies, and testability.","type":"text"}]}]},{"chapters":[{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps"],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Let’s start with a tour of the application we will be building. It’s called SyncUps, and it’s a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recreation of the Apple’s Scrumdinger demo application."}]}],"name":"What is SyncUps?","image":"chapter1.png"},{"image":"chapter2.png","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We will begin building the SyncUps app from scratch by implementing the feature that powers the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"list of sync-ups. It starts out as a simple feature, but it will become increasingly complex as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the app evolves.","type":"text"}]}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ListsOfSyncUps","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingListOfSyncUps"],"name":"Lists of sync-ups"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Let’s build a new feature for editing the details of a sync-up in a form. This will allow us to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"explore the binding tools the library provides, and we will add some complex logic around focus"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in the form, and show how it is 100% testable.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpForm","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpForm"],"name":"New sync-up form","image":"chapter3.png"},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentingSyncUpForm","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation"],"name":"Presenting the sync-up form","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We now have two features built, the sync-ups list and the sync-up form. These features do not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"exist in isolation, but rather are meant to be integrated in a deep way. One should be able to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"navigate to the sync-up form from the list view, enter the details of a new sync-up, and then"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"add that sync-up to the root list.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"image":"chapter4.png"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Applications typically need to persist data across application launches. The Composable","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Architecture comes with tools to help you persist your application’s data."}]}],"image":"chapter5.png","tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PersistingSyncUps"],"name":"Persisting sync-ups to disk"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The next feature to build is the “detail” screen for a sync-up. This feature allows the user to","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"edit a sync-up, record a new meeting, see past recorded meetings, and even delete the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"sync-up."}]}],"image":"chapter6.png","tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetail","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpDetail"],"name":"Sync-up detail"},{"tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetailNavigation","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/MeetingNavigation","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingNavigation"],"image":"chapter7.png","name":"Navigating to sync-up detail","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"We now have a sync-up detail screen, but still no way to navigate to it from the rest of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"app. We want to be able to drill-down to the detail screen from the list screen."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"Record meeting","tutorials":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/RecordMeetingFeature","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingTimer","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer"],"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The app is almost complete! But we have saved the most difficult feature for last: recording"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"a new meeting. This requires interfacing with two complex dependencies, a speech recognizer","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and timer, and requires some subtle behavior that we are definitely going to want to get"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"test coverage on."}]}],"image":"chapter8.png"}],"kind":"volume","image":null,"name":null,"content":[]}],"hierarchy":{"reference":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps","paths":[]},"metadata":{"categoryPathComponent":"BuildingSyncUps","category":"Building SyncUps","title":"Building SyncUps","estimatedTime":"3hr 10min","role":"overview"},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps"},"references":{"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpForm":{"title":"Sync-up form","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupform","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpForm","kind":"project","abstract":[{"text":"We will create a new feature with the Composable Architecture that is capable of editing the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"details of a new sync-up. We will also add some nuanced logic around how focus moves through the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"feature to make things a little more interesting."}],"type":"topic","role":"project","estimatedTime":"15min"},"chapter5.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter5.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter5.png"},"chapter6.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter6.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter6.png"},"chapter7.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter7.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter7.png"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ListsOfSyncUps":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ListsOfSyncUps","kind":"project","title":"Lists of sync-ups","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/listsofsyncups","role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","abstract":[{"text":"We will begin building the SyncUps app from scratch by implementing the feature that powers the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"list of sync-ups. It starts out as a simple feature, but it will become increasingly complex as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the app evolves."}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpDetail":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetail","kind":"project","title":"Sync-up detail","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupdetail","role":"project","estimatedTime":"5min","abstract":[{"text":"The “sync-up detail” screen shows all the information of a sync-up, and has many actions that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"can take place in the screen. The user can edit the sync-up, or start a new meeting in the sync","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"up, or drill-down to a past meeting, or even delete the meeting."}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer":{"title":"Adding a speech recognizer","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/implementingspeechrecognizer","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingSpeechRecognizer","kind":"project","abstract":[{"text":"We have just one feature left to implement, and it’s one of the most complicated ones. We need","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to use Apple’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SFSpeechRecognizer"},{"type":"text","text":" API to ask the user for permission to transcribe their"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"audio, and then start a speech recognition task to live transcribe the meeting while it is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"in progress.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/WhatIsSyncUps":{"title":"What is SyncUps?","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/whatissyncups","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/WhatIsSyncUps","kind":"project","abstract":[{"text":"Let’s start with a tour of the application we will be building. It’s called SyncUps, and it’s a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"recreation of Apple’s Scrumdinger demo application.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"project","estimatedTime":"5min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpForm":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpForm","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupform","title":"Testing the sync-up form","role":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We now have a moderately complex feature for editing the details of a sync-up, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpForm"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"reducer. Let’s get some test coverage on the feature, and doing so will force us to come","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"face-to-face with dependencies for the first time in this tutorial."}],"estimatedTime":"10min","kind":"project","type":"topic"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/MeetingNavigation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/MeetingNavigation","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/meetingnavigation","title":"Navigating to a meeting","role":"project","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Now that we have a navigation stack in place we can start navigating to other features in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"application. The simplest is the meeting screen, which allows you to see the details of a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"previous recorded meeting.","type":"text"}],"estimatedTime":"5min","kind":"project","type":"topic"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/ImplementingTimer":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/ImplementingTimer","kind":"project","title":"Adding a meeting timer","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/implementingtimer","role":"project","estimatedTime":"25min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The first major piece of logic and behavior we will introduce to the record meeting feature is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the timer. This is a long-living effect that runs in parallel with the rest of the feature, and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"we need to implement nuanced logic to figure out when to proceed to the next speaker."}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp":{"title":"Editing and deleting a sync-up","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/editinganddeletingsyncup","identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/EditingAndDeletingSyncUp","kind":"project","abstract":[{"text":"Let’s implement two major pieces of functionality in the detail screen: editing the sync-up and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"deleting the sync-up. This will force us to face a number of common problems in app development","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"all at once, including view reuse, navigation, alerts, and parent-child communication patterns."}],"type":"topic","role":"project","estimatedTime":"30min"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingNavigation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingNavigation","kind":"project","title":"Testing navigation","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingnavigation","role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","abstract":[{"text":"We have now implemented a navigation stack at the root of our application, and integrated","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"3 features into the stack: the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpsList"},{"type":"text","text":" feature, the "},{"code":"SyncUpDetail","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" feature, and the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"MeetingView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Some of these features have quite complex logic binding them together, such as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"when one deletes a sync-up from the detail screen it should pop the screen off the stack."}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpDetail":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpDetail","kind":"project","title":"Testing the sync-up detail","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupdetail","role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"SyncUpDetail","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" feature has slowly become quite complex. It now handles two forms of","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"navigation (an alert and sheet), it models navigation state with a single enum, and it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"updates the parent feature via a shared property. It’s about time we got some test"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"coverage on this feature so we can be sure it works as we expect, and so that we can make future","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"changes with confidence.","type":"text"}]},"chapter1.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter1.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter1.png"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/PresentingSyncUpForm":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PresentingSyncUpForm","kind":"project","title":"Presenting the sync-up form","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/presentingsyncupform","role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"We now have two features built: the sync-ups list and the sync-up form. These features do not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"exist in isolation, but rather are meant to be integrated in a deep way. One should be able to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"navigate to the sync-up form from the list view, enter the details of a new sync-up, and then"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"add that sync-up to the root list."}]},"chapter4.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter4.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter4.png"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/PersistingSyncUps":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/PersistingSyncUps","kind":"project","title":"Persisting sync-ups","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/persistingsyncups","role":"project","estimatedTime":"5min","abstract":[{"text":"Now that we have the ability to add and remove sync-ups from the application, let’s add some","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"persistence. This will involve using the “shared state” tools from the library, such as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Shared"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"fileStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/RecordMeetingFeature":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/RecordMeetingFeature","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/recordmeetingfeature","title":"The RecordMeeting feature","role":"project","abstract":[{"text":"Let’s get the basics of a new feature into place that we can navigate to, and then we will","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"slowly layer on its complex logic and behavior, such as the timer and speech recognizer."}],"estimatedTime":"5min","kind":"project","type":"topic"},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/BuildingSyncUps":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/BuildingSyncUps","kind":"overview","title":"Building SyncUps","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/buildingsyncups","role":"overview","abstract":[{"text":"The SyncUps application is a recreation of one of Apple’s more interesting demo applications,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Scrumdinger. We recreate it from scratch using the Composable Architecture, with a focus on","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"domain modeling, controlling dependencies, and testability."}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/SyncUpDetailNavigation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/SyncUpDetailNavigation","kind":"project","title":"Navigating to a sync-up detail","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/syncupdetailnavigation","role":"project","estimatedTime":"20min","abstract":[{"text":"We will wrap the application built so far in a ","type":"text"},{"code":"NavigationStack","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" so that we can navigate to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the detail screen. To do this we will create a new root-level feature that will be responsible"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for implementing the logic of the stack and integrating all of the features together.","type":"text"}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingSyncUpFormPresentation","kind":"project","title":"Testing the add sync-up flow","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testingsyncupformpresentation","role":"project","estimatedTime":"10min","abstract":[{"text":"We have now integrated two moderately complex features, the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SyncUpsList","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SyncUpForm"},{"type":"text","text":", and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"so its time to write some tests. This will give us the opportunity to prove that the features"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"work in tandem as we expect, and we will explore “non-exhaustive” testing to make our tests less","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"fragile.","type":"text"}]},"doc://ComposableArchitecture/tutorials/ComposableArchitecture/TestingListOfSyncUps":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/tutorials\/ComposableArchitecture\/TestingListOfSyncUps","kind":"project","title":"Testing the list of sync-ups","type":"topic","url":"\/tutorials\/composablearchitecture\/testinglistofsyncups","role":"project","estimatedTime":"5min","abstract":[{"text":"The SyncUpsList feature we have built so far isn’t very complex. In fact, it only has one","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"primary action, that of deleting sync-ups from its collection. However, it can be good practice","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to test new features as you add them, and in the future we will have much more complicated"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"behavior to test."}]},"chapter8.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter8.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter8.png"},"chapter3.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter3.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter3.png"},"chapter2.png":{"alt":null,"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/ComposableArchitecture\/chapter2.png"}],"type":"image","identifier":"chapter2.png"}}}